cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel class of kernels for nonparametric learning with kernel methods that addresses the high computational cost of large-scale data. The paper discusses the use of the proposed kernel for regression and classification tasks, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of the Nyström method, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS) for approximating kernel matrices. Finally, the paper discusses the reduction in computational complexity achieved by the proposed kernel, which is a common concern in neural networks (cs.NE) and other areas of machine learning.
